<center><font size="+2"> Silrais DBExplorer : simple and
smart database objects explorer. </font></center>
<table align="center">
	<tr>
		<th class="leftalign">What is Silrais DBExplorer?</th>
	</tr>
	<tr class="lineitemA">
		<td>Silrais DBExplorer is a web-based database objects browser
		tool with many useful and differentiating features.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<th>&nbsp;</th>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<th class="leftalign">Who Silrais DBExplorer is for?</th>
	</tr>
	<tr class="lineitemA">
		<td>Silrais DBExplorer is for database application developers, qa
		engineers, system analysts, database administrators, technical leads
		and architects.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<th>&nbsp;</th>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<th class="leftalign">What Silrais DBExplorer can do for you?</th>
	</tr>
	<tr class="lineitemA">
		<td>Well, Silrais DBExplorer provides many useful,
		differentiating and advanced features that tools of similar type don't
		provide, such as <br>
		<ol>
			<li>You can click through entities that are related via defined
			foreign keys and browse the hierarchy/tree of entities</li>
			<li>You can click through table data records of related entities
			and browse through the hierarchy/tree of records</li>
			<li>You can define custom views using "parameterized template
			queries in a xml file" and host them to share them with team mates</li>
			<li>You get other standard features of such database tools such
			as lists and details of database objects such as table, view, index,
			procedures, session, data, keys and constraints, etc</li>
			<li>You can configure multiple data-sources in
			'jdog-datasources.properties' found in DBExplorer/WEB-INF/classes to
			configure your databases</li>
			<li>You can configure default data-sources in
			'jdog.properties' found in DBExplorer/WEB-INF to
			configure your default database</li>
			
		</ol>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<th class="leftalign">Default Database</th>
	</tr>
	<tr class="lineitemA">
